1
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:03,990
Hi, new roommate.

2
00:00:04,380 --> 00:00:08,400
Actually, I’ve heard things
about Yotha from Arc’s friends.

3
00:00:08,430 --> 00:00:10,910
People on the outside
aren’t saying nice things about Yotha.

4
00:00:10,940 --> 00:00:12,410
You’ve grown so much, little brother.

5
00:00:13,870 --> 00:00:15,260
I want to get to know you better.

6
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:16,960
I got an internship.

7
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:19,430
I’ll have to move to Rayong for 3 months.

8
00:00:19,460 --> 00:00:20,640
It’s just Rayong.

9
00:00:20,670 --> 00:00:22,640
Let the feeling of missing do its magic.

10
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:24,880
When you see me,

11
00:00:24,910 --> 00:00:26,440
what’s the first thing you think of?

12
00:00:26,570 --> 00:00:27,100
A dog.

13
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:28,290
Do I really look like a dog?

14
00:00:28,310 --> 00:00:29,070
Oeagle.

15
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,480
Beagle, you jerk.

16
00:00:30,510 --> 00:00:31,810
Looking like a dog

17
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:32,940
is not a bad thing.

18
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:33,900
It’s cute.

19
00:00:37,820 --> 00:00:39,900
The dorm is so quiet.

20
00:00:40,130 --> 00:00:41,530
There’s no one left.

21
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:44,060
When will Monday come?

22
00:00:44,550 --> 00:00:47,320
I want to have friends.

23
00:00:51,630 --> 00:00:53,900
I mean, I want more friends.

24
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,360
A few more.

25
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:04,410
Hello.

26
00:01:05,660 --> 00:01:06,730
No, I’m not doing anything.

27
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:07,660
I’m at my dorm.

28
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:09,610
Sure,

29
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:12,800
but can I bring Gun?

30
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:15,920
Me?

31
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:16,670
Where are we going?

32
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:17,890
Okay.

33
00:01:18,130 --> 00:01:19,310
See you in half an hour.

34
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,010
Where are we going?

35
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:25,520
Arm invited me out for a meal and a movie.

36
00:01:26,030 --> 00:01:28,030
Maybe he only wants to invite his group.

37
00:01:28,050 --> 00:01:30,120
I don’t like being around
people I’m not close with for too long.

38
00:01:30,140 --> 00:01:31,000
It’s uncomfortable.

39
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,950
Would bringing me help?

40
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,150
I wouldn’t be bringing you if it didn’t.

41
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,120
Go get ready.

42
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,890
We need to be at the mall in half an hour.

43
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:44,100
Does this mean
I’ve been upgraded to your best friend?

44
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,320
Go get ready.

45
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,610
Answer me.

46
00:01:47,630 --> 00:01:48,590
We’re close now, right?

47
00:02:07,610 --> 00:02:10,260
I told you to get ready, Beagle.

48
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,100
Okay.

49
00:04:09,670 --> 00:04:11,010
Hey, Yotha.

50
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:11,820
Hi.

51
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,000
Hey, guys.

52
00:04:13,810 --> 00:04:15,170
Can I tag along today?

53
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:16,610
Of course.

54
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:17,900
The more, the merrier.

55
00:04:21,350 --> 00:04:24,120
What movie should we watch?

56
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:39,820
Why did that dog have to die?

57
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:40,990
I know, right?

58
00:04:42,710 --> 00:04:44,920
The poster looked so cheerful.

59
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:46,740
We shouldn't have fallen for it.

60
00:04:57,370 --> 00:04:58,960
Enjoy, Yotha, Gun.

61
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,160
I won’t hold back then.

62
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,770
Arc, I need to pee.

63
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,370
Go ahead.

64
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:14,400
Does anyone else need to pee?

65
00:05:15,230 --> 00:05:15,870
Me.

66
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:17,910
Wanna go?

67
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:19,730
Let’s go.

68
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:20,600
I really need to pee.

69
00:05:26,130 --> 00:05:27,520
Hey, Yotha.

70
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,320
Yes?

71
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:32,560
I have a favor to ask.

72
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:39,220
Is there anything else you want to do?

73
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,900
Do you want some dessert or maybe walk around?

74
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,420
Hmm.

75
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:44,140
I’m actually up for anything.

76
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,040
Let’s ask Arc and Yotha.

77
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,150
How’s it going?

78
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:50,780
Have you gotten any closer to Yotha?

79
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:57,360
I don’t like being around
people I’m not close with for too long.

80
00:05:57,380 --> 00:05:58,230
It’s uncomfortable.

81
00:05:58,550 --> 00:06:00,000
Would bringing me help?

82
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,120
I wouldn’t be bringing you if it didn’t.

83
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:03,130
Go get ready.

84
00:06:03,150 --> 00:06:04,690
We need to be at the mall in half an hour.

85
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,230
I’m closer to him now.

86
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:10,900
That’s great.

87
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:13,370
I’ve been trying to break down his walls too,

88
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:16,450
but it’s a bit hard, don’t you think?

89
00:06:16,820 --> 00:06:18,100
It’s really hard.

90
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:21,460
I’m looking for the right moment to warn him about that.

91
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:24,870
But at least Yotha said he wouldn’t lie.

92
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:27,600
If he doesn’t want me to know something,
he just won’t tell me.

93
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:28,620
That’s it.

94
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:31,100
So mysterious.

95
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:35,570
In the second semester,

96
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,230
I’m going to intern in another city.

97
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:39,010
While I’m away,

98
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,470
just don’t get my boyfriend into trouble.

99
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,210
What do you mean?

100
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,940
When you get into fights while I’m here,

101
00:06:48,970 --> 00:06:50,700
I can help settle things.

102
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:53,890
Okay, yes, I’m worried about my boyfriend.

103
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:57,180
I know that if he finds out you’re in trouble,

104
00:06:57,210 --> 00:06:58,570
he won’t just stand by.

105
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:03,710
Yotha, I understand it’s your personal life,

106
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:06,950
and I’m not here to tell you what to do or not to do.

107
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,160
It’s fine if you don’t love yourself

108
00:07:10,910 --> 00:07:12,910
but you need to look at the people around you

109
00:07:12,930 --> 00:07:14,600
and how much trouble you’re causing them.

110
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,880
Don’t wait until you’re hurt

111
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,700
because it’s too late to fix anything.

112
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:27,890
Thank you for warning me.

113
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:30,520
Yeah.

114
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:42,210
Why are you all here today?

115
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:43,520
It’s my bar too.

116
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,660
Can’t I come in and check on things?

117
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,550
Normally, you leave me to run it alone.

118
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,890
I just came to visit.

119
00:07:49,910 --> 00:07:52,170
He’s the one you should ask.

120
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,460
He’s been drinking nonstop.

121
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,130
Did you fight with Klao again?

122
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:00,170
As usual.

123
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:02,730
You should try dating someone older instead.

124
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,730
With Yotha, who’s several years younger than you,

125
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,100
I can understand.

126
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:09,070
But Klao is only a few years younger,

127
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:10,720
and you still can’t communicate.

128
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,720
Are you trying to break us up?

129
00:08:14,890 --> 00:08:15,840
Tell me honestly.

130
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,410
Are things really good with Klao

131
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,410
or are you just dating him to forget Yotha?

132
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,700
Are you guys crazy?

133
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:25,400
I met Klao long after breaking up with Yotha.

134
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:27,490
Klao and Yotha are different.

135
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,220
Do whatever you want.

136
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,870
I can always drink with you.

137
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:33,450
Come on. Cheers.

138
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:38,180
Hey.

139
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,230
I said we should talk tomorrow.

140
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,820
Can’t I come to apologize?

141
00:08:54,190 --> 00:08:54,970
What?

142
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,070
I was being hot-headed.

143
00:08:57,990 --> 00:08:59,990
I was acting like a child,
which is what you don’t like.

144
00:09:01,830 --> 00:09:02,830
I feel guilty,

145
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:05,660
so I wanted to come here and apologize.

146
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:09,260
But if you don’t want to hear it today,

147
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,210
I can come back another day.

148
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:16,540
Klao.

149
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,180
I didn’t drive here today.

150
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:39,570
Then I’ll give you a ride.

151
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:10,850
My fried chicken doesn’t taste good anymore.

152
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,730
Just like me, it’s like yesterday’s leftovers.

153
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,050
Those two are always like that.

154
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:16,800
You know it.

155
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:17,610
Yeah,

156
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,880
I’ll mind my own business next time.

157
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:31,280
I thought this weekend would be boring.

158
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:34,310
Thanks for inviting me out.

159
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,230
You can take a shower first.

160
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:41,630
I’ll just lie down and be lazy for five minutes.

161
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,960
I’m still not used to seeing you in that pajama set.

162
00:10:59,470 --> 00:11:00,210
What’s wrong with it?

163
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:02,990
It doesn’t suit you at all.

164
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:11,080
What?

165
00:11:11,290 --> 00:11:13,880
I want to know if yellow suits Beagle.

166
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:21,880
What do you think?

167
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:24,490
Does this tiger-printed pajama set suit a dog like me?

168
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:29,360
But I think I wear it better than you.

169
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:30,530
You think?

170
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:37,770
Don’t I look handsome?

171
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,400
Can I keep this pajama set?

172
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,300
Why?

173
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:54,210
I’ll wear it when you’re in a bad mood.

174
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:05,670
What did you say?

175
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,140
Well,

176
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:12,640
you just smiled widely
for the first time since we’ve known each other.

177
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,950
Can you smile more often?

178
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:17,280
I like it.

179
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:21,390
No one has ever said anything like that to me.

180
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:23,630
Why?

181
00:12:24,590 --> 00:12:25,710
You don’t like it?

182
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:27,870
Are you going to punch me?

183
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,710
No one has ever paid attention to me

184
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,250
or noticed how I feel.

185
00:12:34,010 --> 00:12:36,960
I don’t know what you’ve been through

186
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,910
but if you try opening up,

187
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:43,900
I’ll find many more ways to make you smile.

188
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:44,700
Okay?

189
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:48,600
Why are you doing this?

190
00:12:58,140 --> 00:12:59,380
Well…

191
00:13:01,790 --> 00:13:02,800
Well…

192
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:03,690
Well what?

193
00:13:04,730 --> 00:13:07,200
I just want to make the people around me happy.

194
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:16,910
Am I one of the people around you?

195
00:13:18,460 --> 00:13:19,660
Why are you asking this?

196
00:13:20,430 --> 00:13:21,510
Just answer.

197
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:24,680
Of course, you are.

198
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:29,120
The people next to me,

199
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,350
in front of me,

200
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,550
or behind me

201
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,670
are all people around me.

202
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,120
Do you care about me?

203
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,770
What?

204
00:13:51,660 --> 00:13:52,490
Forget it.

205
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:53,600
Let’s sleep.

206
00:13:54,370 --> 00:13:55,870
Don’t have nightmares, Beagle.

207
00:13:57,130 --> 00:13:57,690
Oh.

208
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:02,330
Okay.

209
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:03,720
Don’t have nightmares.

210
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:08,840
There, you’re secretly looking at me.

211
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:11,040
Close your eyes already.

212
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:15,590
Beagle.

213
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:26,740
You guys heard they’re making us start wearing

214
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:29,320
the jacket in the second semester this year, right?

215
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:30,080
Really?

216
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,420
I didn’t know.

217
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,360
How come?

218
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:34,990
It’s all over our group chat.

219
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:35,890
Do you ever read the messages?

220
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:36,660
No.

221
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,310
It’s a lot. I’m too lazy.

222
00:14:38,330 --> 00:14:39,880
Come on.

223
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:41,280
That’s good.

224
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:43,450
We’ll look cool one semester early.

225
00:14:43,470 --> 00:14:44,630
Nothing can make you look cool.

226
00:14:44,660 --> 00:14:47,380
Whoa.

227
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,130
Just kidding.

228
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:50,140
His brows are twitching.

229
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,120
I’m just kidding.

230
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:52,330
That’s harsh.

231
00:14:53,090 --> 00:14:54,800
Just kidding.

232
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:56,610
Beagle.

233
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:58,570
Hmm? What’s up?

234
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,000
Hi, Yotha.

235
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:05,400
Hi, Yotha.

236
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:06,910
Tie my necktie for me.

237
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:08,850
Sure.

238
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,140
What did he just call him?

239
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,880
Beagle.

240
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,410
I was looking for your tie this morning.

241
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:21,690
I was going to tie it for you as usual.

242
00:15:21,710 --> 00:15:23,410
- I think I heard that somewhere.
- But I couldn’t find it

243
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,990
and I didn’t want to open your closet.

244
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,430
It’s a dog’s name.

245
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:36,550
Is he using our friend as a dog?

246
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:41,430
Done.

247
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:42,650
You look handsome now.

248
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:55,610
Is this

249
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,200
What you two

250
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:57,560
Normally do?

251
00:15:58,620 --> 00:15:59,440
Yeah.

252
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:00,560
Why are you guys shocked?

253
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:03,510
Damn, Gun.

254
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:05,390
You’re so brave.

255
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:08,620
Yotha walking over here just now

256
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,630
gave me goosebumps already.

257
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:13,530
Don’t you feel uncomfortable around him?

258
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:15,920
Are you sure this is normal, Ears?

259
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,410
We’re roommates.

260
00:16:18,430 --> 00:16:19,750
We sleep in the same room every night.

261
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:20,840
It’d be weird if that didn’t make us close.

262
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,120
Come on. Get up.

263
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,270
We don’t want to be late for the attendance check.

264
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:26,930
Let’s go.

265
00:16:30,130 --> 00:16:31,720
Come on. Get up.

266
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:32,570
Okay.

267
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,120
Why does he have to call him Beagle?

268
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:35,070
Come on!

269
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:36,300
Coming!

270
00:16:42,570 --> 00:16:43,870
Hey.

271
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:45,900
I thought I wouldn’t see you guys in class again.

272
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:48,240
We’ve seen you for three weeks.

273
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:50,050
You just haven't seen us.

274
00:16:50,410 --> 00:16:51,720
Sorry.

275
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,370
I just have so many friends.

276
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,620
Of course.

277
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:56,870
Only the uni president is not your friend.

278
00:16:57,330 --> 00:16:58,330
I have his LINE ID.

279
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:58,920
What?

280
00:16:58,940 --> 00:17:00,030
But he rarely replies to me.

